Package: picosignet
Architecture: any
Depends: libc6
Recommends: openssh-client
Suggests: picotool
Description: host CLI and bridge daemon for the PicoSignet RP2350 SSH CA HSM
 PicoSignet is an RP2350-based USB security key that acts as an SSH
 certificate-signing HSM. This package provides the host-side picosignet
 tool: a bridge daemon that exposes the device over VSOCK/TCP/Unix for the
 cerberus ssh-cert-api service, plus a provisioning and management CLI.
 .
 Only the workstation-side binary is packaged; the RP2350 firmware is
 cross-built and flashed to the device separately.
 .
 A udev rule grants the logged-in user access to the device's CDC-ACM serial
 port (USB 1209:000a) without requiring root or dialout/uucp group changes.
